						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 5) built into the wall of the well called Jēḍara-bāvi.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">17th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The information of this record is the same as in No. 325 above. The additional information of this record is that it states that Tiṁmaya who constructed the well, was the son of Gavuḍa-Dupada-Chiṭapa of Sarjāpura.</p>						

						<p>The date is the same as in No. 325.</p>						

						</summary>
